"{'model': 'mistral:latest', 'response': '\"{ \\\\\"title\\\\\": \\\\\"Capitalize First Letter of Each Word\\\\\", \\\\\"description\\\\\": \\\\\"Write a function `capitalize_words` that takes a string as input and returns the same string with each word capitalized. The words are separated by any number of spaces, commas or periods. If the input is empty or contains only whitespaces, return an empty string.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n#### Function Signature\\\\\\\\n```python\\\\\\\\ndef capitalize_words(s: str) -> str:\\\\\\\\n```\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n#### Input\\\\\\\\n- `s` (str): A string containing words separated by spaces, commas or periods.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n#### Output\\\\\\\\n- Returns the same string as input but with each word capitalized.\\\\\", \\\\\"code\\\\\": \\\\\"def capitalize_words(s: str) -> str:\\\\\\\\n    # Remove non-alphabetic characters and split into a list of words\\\\\\\\n    words = [word.strip() for word in s.split() if word.strip()]\\\\\\\\n    # Capitalize each word and join back together\\\\\\\\n    return \\' \\'.join(capitalize(word) for word in words)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\ndef capitalize(word: str) -> str:\\\\\\\\n    # Capitalize the first letter of the word and return\\\\\\\\n    return word[0].upper() + word[1:]\\\\\", \\\\\"tests\\\\\": [\\\\\"assert capitalize_words(\\'hello world\\') == \\'Hello World\\'\\\\\", \\\\\"assert capitalize_words(\\'a, b, c, d\\') == \\'A, B, C, D\\'\\\\\", \\\\\"assert capitalize_words(\\'.,. .,. . .\\') == \\'.,. .,. . .\\'\\\\\", \\\\\"assert capitalize_words(\\'\\') == \\'\\'\\\\\", \\\\\"assert capitalize_words(\\'   \\') == \\'\\'\\\\\"] }\"'}"